```

This function works by creating a 2D table `dp` where `dp[i][j]` stores the length of the LCS of the substrings `s1[0..i-1]` and `s2[0..j-1]`. It then fills the table in a bottom-up manner and constructs the LCS from the table. The time complexity of this function is O(m*n), where `m` and `n` are the lengths of the input strings.

